docker cli commands-->
docker version 
for checking version

docker ps 
for listing running containers

1 docker pull redis
to pull the redis image

2 docker run --name my-redis -d redis 
to run a redis container 

docker images
to know about the images

3 docker ps
to check running containers

4 docker  exec -it my-redis redis-cli
 to access redis

5 docker stop my-redis
to stop the redis container
 but stop the container not delete it

6 docker start my-redis
to restart the redis container

7 docker rm my-redis
to remove the redis conatainer

8 docker rmi redis
to remove redis image


inside Dockerfile
FROM redis-latest
CMD["redis-server"]

1 docker build -t redisnew .
builds a docker image using the docker file with a name redisnew

2 docker run --name myredisnew -d redisnew 

3 docker ps

4 docker stop myredisnew

5 docker login
 6 docker ps -a 
shows all container including the stopped one

7  docker commit 0e993d2009a1 budarajumadhurika/redis1

8 docker images

9 docker push budarajumadhurika/redis1
uploads image into docker hub so others can download it 

docker tag redisnew docker.io/sushmitha1/redis:latest
docker push docker.io/sushmitah277/redis:latest
